      <trans-unit id="11737" identifier="f17e7b5da610295808d4668fae87df1b">
        <source>Key questions</source>
        <target>crwdns11737:0crwdne11737:0</target>
        <note>Context: Headline 2&#13;
XPath: /h2</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11738" identifier="9cac61d49c549857008180c607440b45">
        <source>Imagine 31 numbers have been organised in ascending order in a list by a computer program.</source>
        <target>crwdns11738:0crwdne11738:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11739" identifier="ffb5c6d939cfe9a5305d5512d834f724">
        <source>Now the program has to find a number in the list, but it can only look at one number at a time.</source>
        <target>crwdns11739:0crwdne11739:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11740" identifier="57aba0ed88f8046e69ee3457566b451c">
        <source>Is it easier to find the number now, than if they were in a random order?</source>
        <target>crwdns11740:0crwdne11740:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11741" identifier="99b0f7b08a0fea55d9673bbf7f187851">
        <source>Potential answers could include:</source>
        <target>crwdns11741:0crwdne11741:0</target>
        <note>Context: Headline 3&#13;
XPath: /h3</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11742" identifier="22125f2cd0b78b4d6163fdb32f24ae14">
        <source>The information is organised in a way that makes it more efficient to find.</source>
        <target>crwdns11742:0crwdne11742:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11743" identifier="ce9fe2e7dfd1f9d52a0e7317eca88fb2">
        <source>By guessing one number and checking it, you can use logical thinking to eliminate the numbers below or above the number guessed because you know the numbers are in order.</source>
        <target>crwdns11743:0crwdne11743:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15555" identifier="b2162d57b0e0823712acfc0432bd2f42">
        <source>{image file-path=&quot;img/topics/child_in_numbers.png&quot; alt=&quot;A child lost in a pile of random numbers.&quot;}</source>
        <target>crwdns15555:0crwdne15555:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /p[2]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15556" identifier="d304696c2070753e4f44ec3f2ee2b5d4">
        <source>If they are in random order you can't use a strategy to find them quickly.</source>
        <target>crwdns15556:0crwdne15556:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul[2]/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11745" identifier="4460fd52c3ef567c91cd109657e20025">
        <source>Lesson starter</source>
        <target>crwdns11745:0crwdne11745:0</target>
