      <trans-unit id="15557" identifier="6a05a69927d8db8be645fd8b4d53bc61">
        <source>We have 31 different numbers, one on each card.</source>
        <target>crwdns15557:0crwdne15557:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15558" identifier="8069d273bfb2d059949cf02dc8891410">
        <source>You can’t see them but this time they are in order from the lowest number to the highest number.</source>
        <target>crwdns15558:0crwdne15558:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15559" identifier="570389e9d57d1956257b51a66d05c55e">
        <source>The numbers range from 0 to 1000.</source>
        <target>crwdns15559:0crwdne15559:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15560" identifier="951c4591e12140654654bbc2eae19fcc">
        <source>Can you find number &lt;strong&gt;302&lt;/strong&gt;</source>
        <target>crwdns15560:0crwdne15560:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15561" identifier="ec11893929d653a46f4f0bd4eb8af6b8">
        <source>{panel type=&quot;teaching&quot; title=&quot;Teaching observations&quot;}</source>
        <target>crwdns15561:0crwdne15561:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /p[4]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15562" identifier="275ca474025d387d04dcb80f11e9b66d">
        <source>You can adapt the range to suit what your students are working on in their mathematics lessons.</source>
        <target>crwdns15562:0crwdne15562:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[5]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15563" identifier="5f26c451a545f8805c70e3930decd8a0">
        <source>This lesson focuses on sorted lists and we are using a range of numbers from 0 - 999.</source>
        <target>crwdns15563:0crwdne15563:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[5]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15564" identifier="06648400d0e61169a3efbe6c3ff13713">
        <source>This activity works best if the numbers &lt;strong&gt;aren’t&lt;/strong&gt; sequential because, for example, if there are 50 cards in the range 1 to 50 and they are sequential and you ask a student to find the number 10 they will probably just look at the 10th card straight away!</source>
        <target>crwdns15564:0crwdne15564:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[5]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15565" identifier="fbd5979a683dc2a908aa543e7648cd14">
        <source>You can generate different sets of cards with various ranges of numbers &lt;a href=&quot;'resources:resource' 'searching-cards'&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.</source>
        <target>crwdns15565:0crwdne15565:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[5]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15566" identifier="af6639ae1d131752852c51ffd3ec5641">
        <source>It's best if the numbers aren't spread evenly so that it's very hard to guess where a particular value might be.</source>
        <target>crwdns15566:0crwdne15566:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[5]</note>
